reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars feel mouth so fresh
reviews.reviewText: This mouthwash is really effective. After using it for a few days, I feel that my teeth are less sensitive, and my teeth have become whiter and brighter. My breath is also very fresh. I like the taste very much. It is not very irritating and is very gentle. I think this mouthwash is very helpful in repairing tooth enamel. I have always had problems with tooth sensitivity and acid erosion, so I bought this mouthwash to try. I didn’t expect it to be so effective. After using it for less than a week, I found that my teeth no longer hurt so much, and the color of my teeth was also better. It has also become more uniform and not as yellow as before. The taste of this mouthwash is also very good, very refreshing, not as spicy as some mouthwashes, which makes me feel very comfortable. I think this mouthwash is the best one I have ever used. It can not only reduce tooth sensitivity, but also repair tooth enamel and protect tooth health. I am very satisfied.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This mouthwash has a mint flavor that lasts a good half an hour after rinsing. Compared to my other mouthwash, I feel like it leaves a layer of coating on my teeth because my teeth feel smoother afterward. It is alcohol-free, so there is no burning sensation. Also, the fact that it protects against cavities and helps repair enamel is a plus. Although, I will leave that up to my dentist to determine at my next visit.Make sure to not drink or eat anything for half an hour after using it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I don’t typically use mouthwash but my dentist mentioned that my enamel was wearing away so I’m looking for ways to manage it.I do love the color, it’s so calming. It tastes great and not overly minty that it is unbearable for a minute of swishing and swirling in your mouth. Definitely feel that my teeth is coated after using. It advises not to drink or eat 30 minutes after rinsing.Hoping this will help manage my worn enamel to prevent further damage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Pronamel Intensive Enamel Repair Mouthwash
reviews.reviewText: Light, refreshing mint flavor without being overpowering. These are alcohol-free so there is no burning sensation while using these. They leave my mouth feeling fresh, without being tingly or too cold. The recommended use is 10ml once per day for 1 minute, and not to eat or drink for 30 minutes afterwards to give it time to work. If I measure accurately, each bottle should last me about 7 weeks which is fantastic.

reviews.reviewText: Good mouth wash without alcohol. Feels very clean after using. Tastes fresh and leaves a very fresh feeling after swishing. Great that it also includes fluoride, just make sure to not rinse it out with water after using the mouthwash.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a trusted brand and a good value for a three-pack of this mouthwash. My husband has weakened enamel and an aversion to alcohol-based mouthwashes. This was the perfect product for him.The mouthwash isn't aggressive but is refreshing. It helps his breath smell better while also potentially helping protect and repair his enamel. I'm not sure how you're able to see the results of that, but it's nice to know it has that potential.He's been using this mouthwash each day for about a week now and enjoys how gentle it is and how refreshing it makes his mouth feel.
